                        </p>
                    <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Our ‘Talk to the Expert’ session has been built on this foundation, rightly said by author, Ken Poirot. The immense energy and engagement involved between the experts and the students make these sessions very interesting and highly popular, too. </p>
                    <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Last week our Vice Principal, John Gomes spoke to us on the 7 habits of highly effective people. This enriching and enlightening session was interactive, too. Mr. Gomes explained the 7 habits in detail and also spoke about Steven Covey’s Four Quadrants on time management. 
                        </p>
                    <iframe style="display: block; margin: 20px auto" src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1nl93saTOEhMhaxJ-A0fUkbYbQxx0dqaA/preview" width="640" height="480"></iframe>
                    <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">
                        This week we were supposed to have a talk with Mr.Daniel Adkins, the CEO of Curtis University. Mr.Daniel, in his earlier address in 2019 had spoken to the 11th graders regarding ‘What universities look for in undergraduate students?’. He was supposed to give us his insight on ‘Future Jobs’, however, unfortunately a fire broke out during the lunch break on Monday and the session was cancelled. We hope to see you soon, Mr Daniel.
                            
                    </p>
    
