                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Last Thursday we had a very interesting session on genetic engineering with Dr. Luca Comai, a professor of Plant Biology at University of California Davis. He works on induced mutations, polyploidy, dosage variation, centromere function and sex chromosomes. He has been involved in the study of CENH3 for nearly a decade and is currently optimizing genome elimination and developing its use for efficient plant breeding. He spoke to us on how he developed TILLING, which is a functional genomic method based on induced mutations. He made this a very captivating experience by talking and simultaneously drawing and showing us the similarities between a man, an animal and a plant.</p>
                    <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">The Q and A session that followed was  very interesting and informative. A lot of questions regarding genome research were asked. Dr. Luca also gave some very valuable advice to budding scientists and researchers. The session ended on a very fun-filled note with one student wanting to know if humans could ever gain super powers and his reply got us thinking hard.
                    </p>
